Design Tokens Used:
- Width: 360px (fixed)
- MinHeight: 64px
- Padding: spacing.lg (16px)
- BorderRadius: borderRadius.md (8px)
- Shadow: elevation.level3
- IconSize: iconSize.medium (20px)

Notification Types:
1. Info: Blue border, info icon, polite announcement (4s auto-dismiss)
2. Success: Green border, checkmark icon, polite announcement (4s auto-dismiss)
3. Warning: Yellow border, warning icon, polite announcement (6s auto-dismiss)
4. Error: Red border, error icon, assertive announcement (8s or manual dismiss)

Structure:
- Icon (left): Type-specific icon with semantic color
- Content (center): Title + message + optional actions
- Close button (right): Manual dismiss

Accessibility Features:
- AutomationProperties.LiveSetting for screen reader announcements
- Polite: Wait for user to finish (info, success, warning)
- Assertive: Interrupt immediately (errors)
- Clear, descriptive text
- Keyboard accessible close button
- Action buttons when available

Behavior:
- Slide in from top-right (desktop) or bottom (mobile)
- Auto-dismiss after duration (except errors requiring acknowledgment)
- Pause auto-dismiss on hover (desktop)
- Stack multiple notifications (max 3 visible)
- Queue additional notifications
- Newest on top

Animation:
- Slide in: 300ms easeOutQuint
- Auto-dismiss: Fade out 200ms
- Manual dismiss: Slide out + fade 250ms

Position:
- Desktop: Top-right corner, 16px from edge
- Mobile: Bottom of screen, full width minus 16px margins
- Stack vertically with 8px spacing

Best Practices:
- Brief, actionable messages
- Use appropriate severity level
- Provide action buttons when relevant (Retry, View Details, Undo)
- Don't stack too many (max 3 visible)
- Critical errors require manual dismiss
- Group similar notifications
- Show timestamp for persistent notifications

Action Buttons:
- Use HyperlinkButton for inline actions
- Maximum 2 actions per notification
- Clear, verb-based labels (Retry, Undo, View, Dismiss)
- Primary action on left

